                    content: "# The Vanilla JS Problem (The Real DOM)\n\nTo understand why React was invented, we must understand the problem it solves. In traditional web development (Vanilla HTML, CSS, and JS), we interact directly with the Real DOM (Document Object Model).\nImagine a massive family tree representing your website: <html> is the grandparent, <body> is the parent, and inside the body, you have headers, sections, buttons, and paragraphs. This tree is the Real DOM.\nIf you write a standard JavaScript function to change the text of a single <h1> tag when a button is clicked, the browser does something highly inefficient: It re-renders (reloads) large portions of the entire DOM tree. For a simple website, this isn't a problem. But imagine an app like Facebook or WhatsApp Web. If you receive a single new message, you do not want the entire webpage, the sidebar, the header, and the navigation menu to reload just to show one line of text. Direct DOM manipulation is slow, heavy, and resource-intensive."
